p: Another study [ 148] reported antiproliferative activity of eupatilin, a naturally flavonoid extracted from A. princeps, against tumor endometrial cells. This compound inhibited endometrial cells growth via G2/M phase cell cycle arrest, and up-regulated p21 protein, by the inhibition of mutant p53. A. princeps leaf extract also inhibited the proliferation of T lymphocyte and the secretion of IFN-γ and IL-2. Ethanolic extract of this medicinal herb lowered the serum levels of TNF-α, ICAM-1, IL-1ß, and VCAM-1, according to Han et al. [ 149].
